CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1945, pg. 21, reads: "Big Game - Charles H. Wheeler, 7106 Race Street, of the Dora Gun and Rod Club, killed this ten point 250-pound buck. This was reported to be the biggest deer bagged in this State.  Lots of venison for this lucky hunter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Charles H. Wheeler of 7106 Race Street, posed next to dead deer hanging from post in garage
